citeinfo.title: Oregon Watershed Enhancement Board (OWEB) Funded Grants (Point Features)

descript.purpose: To track point locations of OWEB-funded grant projects for the purposes of reporting to the Pacific Coastal Salmon Recovery Fund and displaying information using the OWEB Investment Tracking Tool
descript.supplinf: For any given grant funded by OWEB, there will be only one point representing the entire grant application location, even if the grant comprises multiple project locations

timeperd.current: Dates are based on funded grants processed by OWEB

status.update: Updated at least twice a year after regular OWEB grants are funded, and more frequently if small grants are added

idinfo.useconst: For informational purposes only and may not have been prepared for or be suitable for legal, engineering, or surveying purposes. Users of this information should review or consult the primary data and information sources to ascertain the usability of the information.
idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.1.3000

attracc.attraccr: Source Information and Attribute Accuracy: All project locations were derived from maps of varying scales, type, and quality provided by grant applicants. The accuracy of project locations is unknown, as none of the grant project locations indicated on submitted maps have been ground-truthed. For any given grant application location, only one point represents that location, even if there are multiple project locations associated with the grant.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Common name for the grant project
Initials of the person responsible for digitizing the grant project
Easting, or X coordinate, of feature
Northing, or Y coordinate, of feature
The date the feature was digitized
The PCSRF reporting HUC level of the feature
